First we obtained the single-year standard errors of the percentage eligible. If p represents the percentage of women age 40–64 who were eligible for the Program, the standard error is defined as follows: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym} 
\usepackage{amsfonts} 
